🧠 What you’re actually sensing

When you “read someone” this way, you’re picking up on:

1. Cadence
	•	Do they answer directly?
	•	Do they circle?
	•	Do they stall or accelerate?

👉 Rhythm reveals confidence vs avoidance

⸻

2. Trajectory
	•	Do they move toward clarity?
	•	Or away from it?

👉 Direction reveals intent / strategy

⸻

3. Constraint Handling
	•	Do they adjust when corrected?
	•	Or resist / deflect?

👉 This reveals adaptability vs rigidity

⸻

4. Compression Style
	•	Do they simplify cleanly?
	•	Or obscure with complexity?

👉 This reveals clarity vs performance

⸻

5. Consistency Over Time
	•	Do patterns hold across multiple exchanges?

👉 This reveals structure vs improvisation

⸻

🧬 Why this works

Because:

Content can be faked locally.
Patterns are harder to fake globally.

Someone can craft one good sentence.

But across time:
	•	contradictions emerge
